data.name: Contract_Negotation_description
data.value: The role being played by CJADG in this specific task is twofold. One is, serving as a mediator/arbitrator. As per Proclamation No. 1263/2014, MoJ has a mandate to give decisions on a civil dispute arising between two or more government offices. It also mediate or arbitrate disputes between government institutions against private entities based on consents. The second role is CJADG representing government institutions in negotiation/mediation or arbitration. Moreover, CJADG as per Proclamation No. 943/2008 determines the manner in which the dispute arising between federal government offices are resolved through judicial means or other than court alternative such as negotiation, mediation, arbitration.

data.name: contract_Negotiation_description
data.value: The CJADG provides Contract Negotiation, Drafting, Review and advices relating to matters of contract amendments/revisions and other contract related issues. Contract preparation and review service to government institutions pursuant to proclamation No. 943/2016 and 1210/20202. It participates or advises concerned government bodies in contract preparation and negotiation of mega projects and in other contracts when it believes that public and government interest could be affected.

data.name: Inspection_Followup_description
data.value: All government institutions are required by law to give information on the contracts they enter and all civil cases they might have whatsoever its nature is. So as to know the number of cases they have and also to inspect whether these cases are being properly handled by the institutions in a manner that maintains the public interest, the CJADG visits government institutions in person. Based on the findings, CJADG gives recommendations and follow up the execution of the recommendations. It also directly engages in handling the cases that it selects.

data.name: legal_advice_description
data.value: The CJDG takes the principal advisory role in civil, commercial and investment related legal matters given to the Ministry of Justice. Accordingly, it provides legal advice to the federal, Addis Ababa and Dire Dawa government institutions including public enterprises pursuant to Proclamation No. 943/2016. Legal advice is also among the services the CJADG gives to those people including, children, women, elderly, victims of a crime, etc, who does not have sufficient finance to institute suites before federal courts.

data.name: litigation_description
data.value: Domestic Representation Cases The Directorate General represents the federal government offices in civil litigation. It institutes civil suits on behalf of the federal government office; and represent them in civil litigation where they sue or being sued. It represents victims of crime and citizens who do not have financial capacity to institute civil action under federal court. It represents institutions in an ongoing civil litigation fully or whenever necessary it run cases jointly or may give direction to government offices on their handling, and to entertain the case by their own. It has responsibilities to implement decisions and causes execution of judgment in accordance with law. Handling International Cases It also represents the FDRE government at international judicial and quasi-judicial institutions, litigate in consultation with relevant parties the decision.

data.name: Mandates_Description
data.value:
Mandates

Strategies

1.       Continuing the reform of the institution and building up implementation capacity.

2.       Providing effective, efficient, accessible and predictable justice,

3.       Enabling drafts, codification and consolidation of law supported by research and study.

4.       Giving prior to the activities on the prevention of affiances endangering the constitution, constitutional order and public interest and deterring criminals before the court.

5.       Establishing a system of compensation for victims of crime in civil affairs.

6.       Enabling prisoners abide in law and professional with proper handling and protection of human rights.

7.       Making legal research and study and enhancing awareness of the community in protection of human rights, strengthening the rule of law and supporting for good governance and development. 

8.       Creation public capacity and arrangement, which respect and enforce the law and the system through proving public awareness level by level.

9.       Creating public legal awareness through accelerated dissemination of law.

10.   Enhancing the role of Mass and professional association’s stake holders in the building up of good governance and democratization system.

11.   Ensuring and following up the implementation of the courts decisions

12.   Ensuring whether there are respected legal rights and interests of women. Youth, children, disabled and people who are living with HIV/AIDS.

13.   Establishing a system which ensures professional competence and codes of conduct of advocates to enhance their role in the justice system, making complete and change in to proactive the registration system.

14.   Fully changed in to practice the system of documents authentication and registration.

data.name: Mission_Vision_Detail
data.value:
Mission

“ To see the Federal Attorney General Institution that ensures respect of rule of law and win public and state beliefs with participation of the people in 2024/25.”

 

Vision

“Working as principal advisor and representative of the federal government regarding law; undertake legal reform studies, drafting laws, disseminations and enforcing criminal law; ensuring the implementation of federal laws enacted by the federal government and the consistency of their implementations; Performing as central authority of international relations regarding law, follow up implementation of national human rights action plan; offering the relevant legal aid for citizens who do not have financial capacity and needs special attention; enforcing civil interest of the federal government and the public; supervise and administer advocates licensing; enhancing participations of the society and stake holders; ensuring rule of law by respecting and enforcing the constitution and constitutional order.”

Values

  • Strong belief on rule of law
  • Prioritizing public and government interest
  • Participatory working condition sprit
  • Transparency and accountability
  • Detest corruption and malpractices
  • Readiness for change
  • Working in team sprit
  • Sense of service giving
  • Fairness
  • Efficiency and effectiveness
  • Coordination
  • Rendering expedition, qualified and effective services
